|WKBNAME|000
    clear_shield_callback

|WKBSYNOPSIS|000
    |YK0int|000 |CKBclear_shield_callback|000(|YK0closure|000 |GKBcDepleted|000)
    |YK0int|000 |CKBclear_shield_callback|000(|YK0closure|000 |GKBcDepleted|000,
        |YK0int|000 |GKBiType|000)

|WKBDESCRIPTION|000
    Removes and returns the shield points owned by the exact |GKBcDepleted|000
    closure in the generic pool or optional damage-type pool. This is explicit
    cleanup, so it does not invoke the callback.

    The same retained closure passed to |CKBadd_shield|000() must be used.

    |CKBclear_shield_callback|000() is defined in /secure/living.c

|WKBSEE ALSO|000
    |CKBadd_shield|000(L), |CKBquery_shield_callback|000(L),
    |CKBremove_shield|000(L)
